This paper deals with the problem of balancing the reconstruction error and Kullback-Leibler divergence in Variational Autoencoders, which is a common issue in machine learning. The paper proposes a new technique that outperforms previous VAE architectures on typical datasets such as Cifar and Celeba. Given this focus on machine learning and image datasets, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
